SD=Customer Campaign Execution
CR= Customer Campaign Procedure
BQs=CandidateSelection Execution Analysis    
Handle the deployment, execution and on-going refinement of a customer campaign. This includes many types of proactive customer campaigns such as up-sell, cross-sell and customer retention. The campaign execution process performs the initial selection and confirmation of candidate customers and includes providing critical feedback on the impact of the campaign to the design unit to support re-calibration and refinement of the specification based on practical experience
A bank implements a targeted cross-sell campaign in the customer servicing center to generate additional sales
Execute a customer campaign (version) and track and respond to impact
CR - Customer Campaign Procedure							BQ 1 - Candidate Selection			BQ 2 - Execution				BQ 3 - Analysis			
In	Up	Co	Ec	Ex	Rq	Re	Up	Ec	Re	In	Up	Rq	Re	In	Up	Rq	Re
InCR Initiate customer campaign processing
UpCR Update details of an active customer campaign
CoCR Control the execution of a customer campaign (e.g. suspend)
EcCR Accept, reject, etc. a customer campaign procedure
ExCR Execute an automated action against an active customer campaign (e.g. order inventory)
RqCR Request manual intervention in a campaign (e.g. add candidate to list)
ReCR Retrieve details about an active customer campaign
UpBQ Update a campaign candidate list (or selection criteria)
EcBQ Accept, reject, etc a candidate list entry
ReBQ Retrieve details about a campaign candidate list
InBQ Initiate a campaign execution task (invoke the campaign)
UpBQ Update details of a campaign execution task
RqBQ Request manual intervention in a campaign execution task (e.g. request specialist support)
ReBQ Retrieve details about a campaign execution task
InBQ Initiate campaign execution analysis (results in delivery of the analysis)
UpBQ Update details of campaign execution activity/performance analysis
ReBQ Request manual intervention in campaign analysis (e.g. collate work product)
ReBQ Retrieve details about customer campaign analysis activity